As a member of the Firmware Audio team that specifies the solutions for mobile handset chips, the candidate will be responsible for the implementation on target of the audio and speech processing part of the solution. This includes the development and the verification of the modules which are either developed in-house or acquired from a 3rd party. Typical modules of the speech processing chain are multi-microphone processing, noise suppression, automatic gain control, and echo cancellation. Typical modules for the audio processing chain include sampling rate conversion, audio equalizer, and dynamic range control.
The candidate will be expected to:
� Test of algorithms on module level and system level
� Investigate further enhancement of the audio implementation based on code analysis
� Support Audio IP integration in customer product
